The paper deals with visual recognition systems and deep neural networks, which are commonly studied in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses active learning and exploration, which are topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper proposes a new principle for deep architectures, which is relevant to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
